translations.web_personal_data_information_modal_lega: Wallapop, SL, (hereinafter, Wallapop), as responsible for the treatment, will treat the data provided in order to communicate it to a professional user outside the Wallapop platform (a real estate agency), who, later, will contact you in order to inform you about their products/services.{$LINE_BREAK}{$LINE_BREAK} The legal basis for the treatment of the aforementioned data is the consent that you have given linked to the fact of having freely provided personal data through this process. The personal data will be kept as long as you do not request its deletion. Once the deletion is requested, the data will be kept blocked preventing its treatment, except for making the data available to the judges and courts, the Public Prosecutor’s Office or the competent Public Administrations, for the demand of possible responsibilities derived from the treatment and only for the statute of limitations thereof (5 years). Once the indicated period of time has elapsed, the data will be deleted.{$LINE_BREAK}{$LINE_BREAK} You can exercise your rights of access, rectification, deletion, opposition, limitation of the treatment, and portability of your data, as well as the revocation, at any time, of the consent given, before Wallapop, CIF No. B-66.04.9057, in Avda. Meridiana 89 6th Floor, 08026, Barcelona (Spain), attaching a photocopy of your ID or equivalent valid identification document. You can also exercise your rights by a communication addressed to: privacy@wallapop.com. Finally, we remind you that you can file a claim with the Spanish Data Protection Agency, if you consider that Wallapop has violated your rights in terms of data protection.”
